abstract: Helen Macdonald On Nature column reflects on nature preserves like Wicken Fen, one of the oldest in Britain; suggests that nature reserves allow for sort of time travel in that they allow humans to indulge in observation of nature that is precluded in most places by modern life.
lead_paragraph: In one of Britain’s oldest nature reserves, Darwin collected beetles and Saxon warlords hid from invaders. But walking there now is much more than a visit to the past.

headline.main: The Living Beauty of Wicken Fen
